cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about visual saliency detection, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also incorporates deep neural networks, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of unsupervised propagation mechanisms and cellular automata also suggests that it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed algorithm on four datasets, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
